value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body in the posterior brain and projections terminating in the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in a cleft between the anterior optic tubercle and the mushroom body lobe junction. A neurite projects medioventrally in the neuropil forming arborizations in the ventral body and then descends out of the brain. The neurites in the ventral nerve cord terminate in the pro-, meso- and metathoracic neuromere. These are likely to be axonal based on morphology.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the anterior superior protocerebrum, in a cleft between the anterior optic tubercle and the mushroom body lobe junction, and a descending projection that innervates all three thoracic neuromeres (Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: Probably a subtype of aSP3 in Lee et al. (2000) - FBrf0128543, since Yu et al. (2010) map this and other clusters to aSP3. Yu et al. (2010) map this to Kimura et al. (2008) AL4, but Cachero et al. (2010) map AL4 to aSP-d.

value.value: Adult male fruitless-expressing neuron with its cell body in the anterior superior protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010). It is intrinsic to the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010). The female equivalent of this cell does not have extensive arbors in the ring structure (Yu et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Yu et al., 2010). It is also a dopaminergic cell of the PAL cluster (Xie et al., 2018).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the posterior inferior protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body in the lateral posterior brain (Yu et al., 2010). It enters the neuropil through a tract opening below that of plP6 (pIP-e) (Yu et a., 2010). Within the neuropil, the neurite travels medially to towards the medial ring of the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010).
Mushroom body neuroblast whose secondary lineage forms a relatively ventral medial part of the calyx (Ito et al., 2013).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast MBp2.
Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004) and develops from some neuroblast MBp2 (FBbt:00110558).
Mushroom body neuroblast whose secondary lineage forms a relatively ventral lateral part of the calyx (Ito et al., 2013).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast MBp3.
Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004) and develops from some neuroblast MBp3 (FBbt:00110561).
Mushroom body neuroblast whose secondary lineage forms a relatively dorsal lateral part of the calyx (Ito et al., 2013).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from neuroblast MBp4.
Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004) and develops from some neuroblast MBp4 (FBbt:00110564).
Region of the cortex that lies laterally in the superior protocerebrum. It contains numerous somata of neurosecretory neurons, divided into 3 groups (Siegmund and Korge, 2001; Velasco et al., 2007).

label.value: adult neurosecretory cell of pars lateralis

value.value: Neurosecretory cell of the adult pars lateralis. It follows the nervus corporis cardiaci II to the ring gland (de Velasco et al., 2007).

label.value: larval neurosecretory cell of pars lateralis

value.value: Neurosecretory cell of the larval pars lateralis. It follows the nervus corporis cardiaci II to the ring gland (de Velasco et al., 2007).

label.value: adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron V

value.value: Adult uniglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron with dendrites that mainly innervate antennal lobe glomerulus V. There are several different morphologies (Lin et al., 2013).

definition.value: Removed lineage assertion as not found in original reference (Lin et al., 2013) - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.

value.value: Neuroblast that delaminates from the optic lobe neuroepithelium during the larval stage (Egger et al., 2007). It generates secondary (adult-specific) optic lobe neurons via asymmetric division (Egger et al., 2007).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron of the aIP-i cluster in the anterior inferior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Not mentioned in Cachero et al. (2010) paper, but clone image data provided to and can be found in Virtual Fly Brain.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from one of the mushroom body neuroblasts.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body in the cell body rind of the mushroom body calyx (Yu et al., 2010) and arbors mostly restricted to the mushroom body (Yu et al., 2010; Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain, all of which develop from the neuroblasts MBp1-4.

definition.value: There are four equivalent lineage clones of this type, MBp1-p4, which develop from one of four neuroblasts (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013).

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that is part of some adult (FBbt:00003004) and develops from some neuroblast MBp (FBbt:00007113).

definition.value: There are four similar neuron lineages of this type, MBp1-p4, which each develop from one of four neuroblasts (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast CREa1. Its cell bodies are located dorsal to the antennal lobe. Neurites project medioventrally, with differences between males and females. Neurites form bilateral dendritic arborizations in the subesophageal zone, and then project dorsally to terminate in lateral junction.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast CREa1 (Ito et al., 2013), has its soma dorsal to the antennal lobe and bilateral dendritic arbors in the subesophageal zone (Yu et al., 2010). It projects dorsally to terminate in the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located junction of the ventrolateral protocerebrum and the antennal lobe. A neurite projects medially and forms two arbors: a dendritic arbor in the lateral junction and an axonal arbor in the anterior medial protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron with its soma in the anterior brain between the antennal lobe and ventrolateral protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). It arborizes ipsilaterally in the superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). It has an additional, more ventromedial arbor compared to the female equivalent (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) map Yu et al. (2010) - FBrf0211884 aSP12 to aSP-j, but Yu et al. (2010) map aSP12 to aDT-d.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast ALl1.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast ALl1 (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 29 of these per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPa1.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast VLPa1 (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 33 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl&d1.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast BLAv1 (VLPl&d1) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 30 of these cells per hemisphere, with somas forming two clusters close to the ventrolateral protocerebrum (Kimura et al., 2008; Cachero et al., 2010; Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: Yu et al. (2010) - FBrf0211884 map aIP1 to Cachero et al. (2010) aIP-d and to AL6b from Kimura et al. (2008) - FBrf0205974, but Cachero et al. (2010) map aIP1 (and AL6b and AL5b) to aIP-c. Ito et al. (2013) - FBrf0221438 also give lineage as VLPl&d1 for aIP-c and AL5b/6b.

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron with its soma in the lateral part of the central brain and a projection that crosses the midline (Cachero et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Yu et al. (2010) - FBrf0211884 map aIP1 to Cachero et al. (2010) aIP-d and to AL6b from Kimura et al. (2008) - FBrf0205974, but Cachero et al. (2010) map aIP1 (and AL6b and AL5b) to aIP-c. Ito et al. (2013) - FBrf0221438 also give lineage as VLPl&d1 for aIP-c and AL5b/6b.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLP2. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region, away from the neuropil and always ventral to aSP-k cell bodies. Neurites project dorsally on the surface of the ventrolateral protocerebrum before entering a tract in the neuropil region below the lateral horn. Unlike aSP-k, the projection from the cell body does not bend before entering the tract. Within the tract, the neurite projects medially arborizing first in the ventral lateral horn, then projects medially to arborize a discrete ventral region in the ring.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron with its soma lateral to the lateral horn, ventral to aSP-k (aSP8), and arborization only in the ipsilateral hemisphere, including the lateral horn (Yu et al., 2010). It develops from neuroblast BLAv2 (VLPl2) (Ito et al., 2013). There are approximately 27 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VLPl_p1. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. A neurite projects medially through the ring and crosses the midline. Another branch projects to the lateral junction.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast BLVp2 (VLPl&p1) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). It has its soma lateral to the brain (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) list aIP-g and pIP-e as corresponding to the Yu et al. (2010) pIP6, with pIP-e additionally corresponding to pIP5.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad1. Its cell bodies located are located in the pars intercerebralis. Projections extend laterally away from the pars intercerebralis and then ventrally to the lateral junction. The extensive arbors span the arch, lateral junction and the medial ring. The axonal arbors are likely to be enriched in the lateral junction. Females have less extensive arbors compared with males.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless-expressing neuron that develops from the SMPad1 neuroblast (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). It has its soma in the pars intercerebralis and projects laterally, arborizing extensively in the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010). Many of these cells are activated by the presence of females, but not males (Takayanagi-Kiya and Kiya, 2019). There are approximately 50-60 of these cells per hemisphere (Lee et al., 2000; Cachero et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad2. Its cell bodies are located in the dorsal pars intercerebralis. Neurites project ventroposteriorly and then bifurcate. One branch projects ipsilaterally and terminates in the medial protocerebrum. The other branch projects ventromedially, turns dorsally at the midline and then joins the path of the same cluster on the contralateral side possibly arborizing in the contralateral hemisphere. The dendritic arbors are likely to be located in the lateral junction while the axonal arbors are in the ventral medial protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult male fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast SMPad2 (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 15 of these cells per hemisphere, with their somas in the pars intercerebralis (Lee et al., 2000; Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Correspondence of Yu et al. (2010) - FBrf0211884 aSP1 to aSP1 in other studies is unclear - they also seem to call this aSP2-p in fig S2 and give contradictory correspondences in table S1. and Cachero et al. (2010) list Yu et al. (2010) aSP1 as possibly corresponding to aSP-b and aSP-c.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior superior protocerebrum. Neurites project ventrally in the dorsal lateral protocerebrum and form arbors extending down to the lateral crescent.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless aSP-f neuron of the male. A subset of these respond to the sex pheromone cVA (Kohl et al., 2013). Unlike their female equivalents, these cells innervate the ventral lateral horn and receive input from projection neurons that receive input in antennal lobe glomerulus DA1 (Kohl et al., 2013).

A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal2. The cell bodies are located away from the neuropil, lateroanteriorly from the lateral horn. A neurite enters a neuropil tract anterior to lateral horn and projects medially to arborize in the lateral junction and the lateral crescent. It also projects to the contralateral hemisphere.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless aSP-g neuron of the male. There are approximately 13 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult male brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DPLal2 (LHl2).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).
